726606f-a.text:
Flushing Meadow Park (Queens): Viewing north across the marshland and an ash road leading to the dump hills on the western edge of the park, seen from near Roosevelt Avenue and 114th Street. This area later became part of the New York World's Fair grounds
of 1939-40.
October, 1935
Views 1,2,3
P. L. Sperr
